article.headline: Evansville 79, Illinois State 48
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Clint Cuffle scored 14 of his 21 points in the decisive first half as Evansville overwhelmed Illinois State 79-48 Wednesday in the Missouri Valley Conference. The visiting Redbirds (6-15, 2-11) played Evansville even for the opening five minutes, taking an 11-10 lead on Najee Echols' free throw. Evansville (5-16, 4-9) then took the lead for good, scoring the next seven points on a Cuffle dunk, a Lucio Wagner jumper and a three-point play by Matt Webster, who had 14 points and seven rebounds in just 17 minutes of foul-plagued action. The Aces held Illinois State to eight points over the final 14:38 of the half and led 38-19 at the break. The Redbirds shot just 25 percent (7-of-28) for the period. Illinois State never got closer than 17 points after that. Echols led Illinois State with 16 points.
